text: The Great Seal of the State of Nebraska was adopted with the legislature of the U.S. State of Nebraska in June 1867. The current has a blacksmith working with an anvil. On the seal's top shows "Equality Before the Law" On its outside the words "Great Seal of the State of Nebraska" are on top. On the bottom is the date "March 1, 1867" (on which Nebraska was officially classified a U.S. State). There are a number of other symbols shown in the State Seal of Nebraska. ==References== Category:United States state seals
title: Seal of Nebraska
